00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:37,840
West passage: 46.7 meters long,

289
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,200
6–30.8 meters wide;

290
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:43,240
East passage: 134.5 meters long,

291
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:46,080
9.7–40.2 meters wide.

292
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:53,880
I asked you to come here
to investigate the cultural relics,

293
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:56,060
and you've discovered

294
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:59,610
a large tomb in the shape
of the character "亚".

295
00:14:01,670 --> 00:14:02,790
This is a big deal.

296
00:14:03,910 --> 00:14:05,240
I need to report this to my superiors.

297
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,080
Director Zhang,

298
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,240
you haven't said yet.

299
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:09,370
Who do you think could be buried there?

300
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:15,670
It's hard to say.

301
00:14:20,030 --> 00:14:23,230
When the black pottery figurines
were first discovered,

302
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:25,530
the academic community discussed this.

303
00:14:26,150 --> 00:14:27,280
Some people thought

304
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:28,910
it might be

305
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:30,490
Princess Guantao's tomb.

306
00:14:31,790 --> 00:14:33,000
But now it seems

307
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:34,870
it's unlikely to be

308
00:14:35,670 --> 00:14:37,120
Princess Guantao's tomb.

309
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,720
Then let me make a bold guess.

310
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:43,260
Could it possibly be
the tomb of Emperor Taizong of Han?

311
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,860
You really dare to guess, kid.

312
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:51,120
You're quite bold.

313
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:52,870
Aren't you afraid that if word gets out,

314
00:14:52,870 --> 00:14:55,270
people will say you're
just making a scene?

315
00:14:56,390 --> 00:14:57,390
For centuries,

316
00:14:57,790 --> 00:15:01,660
everyone has believed Emperor Taizong's
Zi Mausoleum is on Phoenix Mountain.

317
00:15:01,660 --> 00:15:03,380
But we've gone through

318
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:05,670
tons of historical records,

319
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:08,320
and found the saying might be

320
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:10,260
based on a misunderstanding.

321
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:11,890
In fact,

322
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:14,640
it's made me even more convinced

323
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,220
the Zi Mausoleum isn't there.

324
00:15:19,970 --> 00:15:20,500
Let's go.

325
00:15:22,030 --> 00:15:23,960
Let's check out Phoenix Mountain.

326
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,910
In the Records of the Grand Historian,

327
00:15:31,910 --> 00:15:33,670
Emperor Taizong of Han's will said:

328
00:15:33,670 --> 00:15:37,200
"Zi Mausoleum shall follow
the natural landscape, no alterations."

329
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:37,910
That's why

330
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,960
people later believed

331
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:42,080
that the Zi Mausoleum
utilized the original terrain,

332
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,510
without building an earthen mound,

333
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:45,420
using the mountain as the mausoleum.

334
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:45,940
Look,

335
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:48,360
doesn't the Phoenix Mountain

336
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:51,020
look like a flying phoenix
spreading its wings?

337
00:15:53,890 --> 00:15:56,290
That protruding hill

338
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,620
is the phoenix's head.

339
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,300
Looking from afar,

340
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:02,240
the mountain is steep and precipitous,

341
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:04,030
with an extraordinary grandeur.

342
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:05,240
It does look like

343
00:16:05,610 --> 00:16:08,200
a large natural burial mound.

344
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,120
If we consider

345
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:13,670
"not building a mound,
but using a mountain as a mausoleum"

346
00:16:13,670 --> 00:16:16,400
as a criterion for
identifying the Zi Mausoleum,

347
00:16:17,270 --> 00:16:18,510
then I believe the tomb in Yin Village

348
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:20,040
also meets this condition.

349
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:23,500
We've measured it.

350
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:26,700
The tomb in Yin Village
is circular in shape,

351
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,440
with an elevation of
over 750 meters on all sides.

352
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:32,320
It's also the highest point
on the western side of Bailu Plain.

353
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:33,050
According to

354
00:16:34,030 --> 00:16:36,440
Luo Tianxiang's
"Classified Records of Chang'an,"

355
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:40,150
the Zi Mausoleum is near
Phoenix Mountain north of Bailu Plain,

356
00:16:40,630 --> 00:16:41,270
however,

357
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:43,440
Fang Kun and I are doubt about

358
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,670
the academic value of that book,

359
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:48,550
as we haven't found any records

360
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:51,080
of this person in other historical texts.

361
00:16:55,150 --> 00:16:59,010
These stone tablets were erected
during the Ming and Qing dynasties.

362
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:01,920
Why have they stood here
for hundreds of years?

363
00:17:02,390 --> 00:17:03,250
Because people

364
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:04,770
believe in them.

365
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:06,770
In the last century,

366
00:17:06,829 --> 00:17:08,720
many renowned Chinese and foreign scholars

367
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:11,180
came to Phoenix Mountain
for field research

368
00:17:12,069 --> 00:17:13,930
and reached the same conclusion.

369
00:17:14,109 --> 00:17:15,170
They believed that

370
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:18,359
Phoenix Mountain is the Zi Mausoleum.

371
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,680
After the founding of New China,

372
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:24,510
we also conducted
several archaeological studies

373
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:26,950
and finally reached

374
00:17:26,950 --> 00:17:27,579
[Zi Mausoleum of Emperor Taizong of Han]

375
00:17:27,579 --> 00:17:28,780
the same conclusion.

376
00:17:29,830 --> 00:17:31,290
Your speculation is bold.

377
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:32,270
I support

378
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,510
your idea,

379
00:17:37,350 --> 00:17:38,000
but

380
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,420
if you want to topple a scholarly pillar,

381
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,450
you'd better tread carefully.

382
00:17:46,590 --> 00:17:48,590
Do you know how significant this is?

383
00:17:49,070 --> 00:17:49,550
I know.

384
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:54,480
Director Zhang,

385
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:57,580
we know this speculation
is too revolutionary.

386
00:17:59,350 --> 00:18:00,210
If we're right,

387
00:18:00,830 --> 00:18:02,160
we'll correct history.

388
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:03,650
If we're wrong,

389
00:18:04,550 --> 00:18:06,000
we'll be a laughingstock.

390
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,400
It's more than just being a laughingstock.

391
00:18:09,270 --> 00:18:11,640
It will be a forever stain
on your academic career!

392
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:12,500
I'm not afraid.

393
00:18:14,310 --> 00:18:14,970
Me neither.

394
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:26,030
Good.

395
00:18:27,070 --> 00:18:27,750
Good lads.

396
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:34,070
I've always emphasized one thing:

397
00:18:34,510 --> 00:18:35,170
stability.

398
00:18:36,650 --> 00:18:37,550
You two

399
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,310
has brought out my ambition.

400
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:42,410
Alright.

401
00:18:43,240 --> 00:18:45,030
Tell me, what's your plan next?

402
00:18:45,550 --> 00:18:48,510
To reveal the truth,
we must first eliminate the false.

403
00:18:48,510 --> 00:18:49,400
We want to apply

404
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:52,110
for an archaeological
survey of Phoenix Mountain

405
00:18:52,110 --> 00:18:54,640
to see if there's
actually a tomb underneath.

406
00:18:57,960 --> 00:18:59,160
I'll submit a report.

407
00:18:59,710 --> 00:19:00,640
Wait for my news.

408
00:19:01,070 --> 00:19:01,960
Cheers.

409
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,230
What's up? Speak.

410
00:19:11,270 --> 00:19:12,680
Why are you drinking so fast?

411
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:13,720
No, I have to finish this.

412
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:15,250
You're acting weird today.

413
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,000
Being this happy,

414
00:19:17,070 --> 00:19:18,670
you must have some good news.

415
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:22,160
Look.

416
00:19:23,110 --> 00:19:24,440
I'm going to be a father.

417
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,460
It's been 11 weeks.

418
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:50,680
Wen Wen.

419
00:19:51,510 --> 00:19:52,480
Guang's drunk.

420
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:53,680
Help him inside.

421
00:19:54,780 --> 00:19:56,040
Go inside and lie down.

422
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:56,960
Just one more drink.

423
00:19:56,960 --> 00:19:58,000
Come on, up you go.

424
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,140
Get up.

425
00:19:59,350 --> 00:19:59,750
Drink.

426
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,170
Take it easy.

427
00:20:03,510 --> 00:20:04,900
I can walk on my own.

428
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:07,400
Slow down.

429
00:20:34,550 --> 00:20:35,350
What's wrong?

430
00:20:36,590 --> 00:20:37,850
I can't keep this baby.

431
00:20:39,790 --> 00:20:40,240
Hey,

432
00:20:41,110 --> 00:20:42,200
don't be foolish.

433
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,070
What if it's yours?

434
00:20:50,310 --> 00:20:50,920
Remember,

435
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:52,480
this child

436
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:54,600
is yours and Guang's.

437
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:56,880
It's for your own good

438
00:20:57,270 --> 00:20:58,200
to have the baby.

439
00:20:58,790 --> 00:21:00,250
Don't do anything stupid.

440
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:10,880
What brings you here?

441
00:21:11,070 --> 00:21:12,880
What are you doing up there?

442
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,790
I'm checking your electrical wiring.

443
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:19,830
It'll be freezing cold
during the New Year.

444
00:21:19,830 --> 00:21:22,200
It's a pity if you
can't use a small heater.

445
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,350
I appreciate it.

446
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:26,220
But haven't you noticed
it's already been fixed?

447
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:28,820
Yeah, no wonder the circuit
looked different.

448
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:30,890
Who fixed it?

449
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:32,920
Hou Yuelai had someone fix it.

450
00:21:33,590 --> 00:21:34,350
Fine.

451
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,640
He beat me to it, huh?

452
00:21:39,310 --> 00:21:40,160
Again.

453
00:21:40,510 --> 00:21:42,640
Why are you here instead of going home?

454
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:45,010
I'm here to spend the New Year with you.

455
00:21:46,110 --> 00:21:47,710
Don't you have your own home?

456
00:21:49,830 --> 00:21:51,200
I have a home, but I can't go back.

457
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:53,270
My parents gave me a task.

458
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:54,240
What task?

459
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,040
They said,

460
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:59,940
if I don't bring home a girl this year,

461
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,080
I shouldn't bother coming back.

462
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:03,000
Then you'd better go find your girl now.

463
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,110
Why are you staying here?

464
00:22:04,110 --> 00:22:05,480
Besides, I never said you could stay.

465
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:06,880
I don't need your permission.

466
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:07,960
It's not like I'm staying in your room.

467
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,110
You're quite thick-skinned.

468
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:10,480
You want to share a room with me?

469
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:12,200
I didn't say that!

470
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:13,070
What's wrong with you?

471
00:22:13,070 --> 00:22:14,550
-I said I won't stay in your room.
-Ms. Luo.

472
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:15,410
Happy New Year.

473
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:16,560
Fugui.

474
00:22:16,590 --> 00:22:17,030
Fugui.

475
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,240
Mr. Fang is here too.

476
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:18,880
Happy New Year.

477
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:19,550
Let me.

478
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:22,510
Ms. Luo.

479
00:22:23,350 --> 00:22:25,510
I heard you're not
going back for the New Year.

480
00:22:25,510 --> 00:22:27,440
My wife and I made some food for you.

481
00:22:27,510 --> 00:22:28,820
It's not easy being alone away from home.

482
00:22:28,820 --> 00:22:29,640
Work's one thing,

483
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:31,090
but you still need to eat well.

484
00:22:31,090 --> 00:22:32,590
Well, you're too kind.

485
00:22:32,750 --> 00:22:33,920
We're really embarrassed.

486
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:34,790
Please take it back.

487
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:37,110
There's nothing to be embarrassed about.

488
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:39,060
We can't help you with much else.

489
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:40,920
We can only make some food and drinks.

490
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:42,550
Right. They specially prepared these.

491
00:22:42,550 --> 00:22:43,010
Take it.

492
00:22:43,030 --> 00:22:43,560
Alright.

493
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:45,160
I'm leaving. Eat it while it's hot.

494
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:45,510
Bye.

495
00:22:45,510 --> 00:22:45,720
Okay.

496
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:46,350
Let's go.

497
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,310
Happy New Year!

498
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:48,170
Happy New Year!

499
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:48,930
Hurry up.

500
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:56,550
You really know how to
maintain good relationships with people.

501
00:22:56,550 --> 00:22:57,510
So much food.

502
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,240
Why are they being so nice to us?

503
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:01,100
Don't you know?

504
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:04,020
It's all because of the mess you made.

505
00:23:04,220 --> 00:23:07,080
It's just about fixing t
he family temple, isn't it?

506
00:23:07,510 --> 00:23:08,840
Shulan, slow down a bit.

507
00:23:09,750 --> 00:23:10,480
Wait for me.

508
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:12,010
I can't keep up with you.

509
00:23:12,070 --> 00:23:13,830
A heavy heart makes for a heavy body.

510
00:23:13,830 --> 00:23:14,510
Your heart's

511
00:23:14,510 --> 00:23:16,270
too full of messy thoughts—

512
00:23:16,590 --> 00:23:18,120
that's why you're lagging.

513
00:23:18,750 --> 00:23:20,790
Easy for you to say.

514
00:23:21,790 --> 00:23:23,750
It's not my heart that's heavy—

515
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:27,030
it's all this stuff I'm carrying.

516
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:29,030
And it's all to help you.

517
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:31,660
Put it down.

518
00:23:32,470 --> 00:23:33,790
Yeah, let's rest a bit.

519
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:35,550
What's the rush?

520
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:36,880
Who asked you to come?

521
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:38,590
I can carry it myself.

522
00:23:38,590 --> 00:23:40,320
You insisted on coming with me.

523
00:23:40,550 --> 00:23:41,610
Why are you mad now?

524
00:23:42,030 --> 00:23:44,070
Getting grumpier with age.

525
00:23:44,830 --> 00:23:46,480
Can't I even say anything?

526
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:48,110
If you don't want to come, then don't.

527
00:23:48,110 --> 00:23:49,570
Why did you follow me here?

528
00:23:51,350 --> 00:23:53,880
Listen, good thing
Jianhui has a good temper.

529
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:57,320
If it were me,
I would've divorced you already.

530
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:58,720
You seem quite close now.

531
00:23:58,720 --> 00:24:00,520
Now you're speaking nice of him.

532
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:02,550
You weren't like this before.

533
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,680
We're all family.

534
00:24:06,310 --> 00:24:07,720
No need to hold grudges.

535
00:24:08,350 --> 00:24:08,880
Right?

536
00:24:10,270 --> 00:24:11,130
Let me tell you,

537
00:24:11,270 --> 00:24:12,680
if you keep making a fuss like this,

538
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,240
one day Jianhui might really leave.

539
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,160
Let's see how you'll manage then.

540
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:16,480
Relationships come and go

541
00:24:16,480 --> 00:24:17,410
in a natural way.

542
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:18,970
If you two get divorced,

543
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:19,960
you'll really become

544
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:21,690
the disgrace of our Liu family.

545
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:25,070
Now you're talking to me about disgrace?

546
00:24:25,270 --> 00:24:27,480
Look at the immoral things you've done.

547
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:30,010
You've embarrassed our whole family.

548
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:31,960
You're kneading it well.

549
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:32,960
Madam Liu is here.

550
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,960
Madam Liu!

551
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:37,730
Jianhui.

552
00:24:38,590 --> 00:24:39,920
What are you doing here?

553
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:43,310
Uncle Mu is teaching me
to make golden-thread pastries.

554
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:44,160
Shulan.

555
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,790
Why did you come here?

556
00:24:46,790 --> 00:24:48,030
What kind of question is that?

557
00:24:48,030 --> 00:24:49,750
He's obviously here waiting for you.

558
00:24:49,750 --> 00:24:50,650
Did I ask you?

559
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:52,070
Fine, I'll stay out of it.

560
00:24:52,070 --> 00:24:52,800
You two talk.

561
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,200
Come on, kids!

562
00:24:54,480 --> 00:24:55,550
Time for presents!

563
00:24:55,550 --> 00:24:56,270
Come here.

564
00:24:56,270 --> 00:24:57,400
Presents are here.

565
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:57,960
No pushing!

566
00:24:57,960 --> 00:24:58,640
Go quickly.

567
00:24:59,110 --> 00:24:59,920
No pushing!

568
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:01,700
Come on, everyone line up.

