00:25:02,270 --> 00:25:02,790
Shulan.

570
00:25:03,510 --> 00:25:04,370
Give it to me.

571
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:07,880
This is for you. Take it. Here.

572
00:25:08,310 --> 00:25:10,070
You're not happy that I came.

573
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:12,010
Why should I be happy or not?

574
00:25:13,030 --> 00:25:15,160
Whether you're sincere or not,

575
00:25:15,550 --> 00:25:17,520
just showing up is a kind act.

576
00:25:18,060 --> 00:25:20,060
And I won't turn your kindness away.

577
00:25:22,310 --> 00:25:23,680
Once the dough's ready,

578
00:25:24,030 --> 00:25:25,480
help me finish the pastries.

579
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:27,030
Haven't made these in years—

580
00:25:27,030 --> 00:25:28,090
my hands are rusty.

581
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:31,020
If you don't want to go home this year,

582
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:32,360
let's just stay here.

583
00:25:32,490 --> 00:25:33,420
I'll be with you.

584
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:37,380
Then...

585
00:25:37,830 --> 00:25:39,720
let's give the kids their presents first.

586
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:40,160
Right,

587
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,110
the presents.

588
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:44,200
I'm so slow at knitting.

589
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:45,440
All thumbs.

590
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:48,880
I was hoping to finish this vest

591
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:52,200
by the time our baby's born.

592
00:25:53,070 --> 00:25:53,920
It'll be a gift

593
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:56,070
from his dad.

594
00:25:59,350 --> 00:26:00,550
Don't close it for me,

595
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:03,000
I'm still learning.

596
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:06,160
One wrong stitch messes everything up.

597
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:08,120
Look, I just got to this part—

598
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:08,640
Here.

599
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:15,160
This stitch.

600
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:18,750
Don't look at me.

601
00:26:19,350 --> 00:26:20,880
Look at the New Year poster.

602
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:23,310
The seller said the more

603
00:26:23,880 --> 00:26:24,830
you look at it,

604
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:26,000
the more your baby

605
00:26:26,110 --> 00:26:27,950
will look like the poster baby.

606
00:26:28,110 --> 00:26:28,880
So cute.

607
00:26:31,420 --> 00:26:33,550
Have you thought of a name for the baby?

608
00:26:35,510 --> 00:26:36,240
If it's a boy,

609
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:38,060
call him Niannian.

610
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:39,520
If it's a girl,

611
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:40,810
call her Huahua.

612
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:44,500
What's wrong with you?

613
00:26:44,880 --> 00:26:45,940
Can you be serious?

614
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:48,440
Naming the baby's a big deal.

615
00:26:49,030 --> 00:26:50,000
I bought a New Year poster
("Nianhua" in pinyin),

616
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,400
and you said calling them
Niannian and Huahua.

617
00:26:51,400 --> 00:26:52,530
What if I buy a paomo?

618
00:26:52,830 --> 00:26:55,160
One called Paopao, the other called Momo?

619
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:56,770
I can't think of one.

620
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:57,700
You try.

621
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:04,590
If it's a girl,

622
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:07,440
call her Dandan.

623
00:27:09,070 --> 00:27:10,030
If it's a boy,

624
00:27:10,750 --> 00:27:11,680
call him Dandan.

625
00:27:14,990 --> 00:27:16,960
That's even worse
than Niannian and Huahua.

626
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,030
Dandan, Dandan.

627
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:19,420
Or

628
00:27:19,790 --> 00:27:21,320
let's have Mu name the baby.

629
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:22,960
Why him?

630
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,440
Mu is educated, you know.

631
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:26,160
He's not an outsider, like our brother.

632
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:27,020
Why not let him?

633
00:27:27,030 --> 00:27:27,960
This is my baby.

634
00:27:29,200 --> 00:27:30,440
I know it's your baby.

635
00:27:31,070 --> 00:27:33,130
But Mu is like the child's godfather.

636
00:27:33,510 --> 00:27:35,570
That's close enough to a real father.

637
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:42,440
I... I was wrong.

638
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:45,400
Pregnant women shouldn't get angry.

639
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:46,660
What's wrong with you?

640
00:27:48,830 --> 00:27:50,510
After you're pregnant, you get mad

641
00:27:50,510 --> 00:27:51,440
so easily these days.

642
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:52,110
Alright.

643
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,270
I'll stop talking, okay?

644
00:27:53,270 --> 00:27:54,400
I'll think of a name.

645
00:27:55,770 --> 00:27:56,370
Ms. Luo,

646
00:27:58,070 --> 00:27:59,130
the paste is ready.

647
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:02,040
How's the couplet coming along?

648
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:03,970
Just finished the last stroke.

649
00:28:04,330 --> 00:28:06,090
There, top line's done.

650
00:28:06,350 --> 00:28:07,240
Look, how's it?

651
00:28:08,830 --> 00:28:10,160
Your handwriting is...

652
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:12,940
not bad.

653
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,110
It won't be embarrassing to put it up.

654
00:28:14,110 --> 00:28:15,030
Not embarrassing?

655
00:28:15,030 --> 00:28:16,480
This is something to be proud of.

656
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:18,070
What's this? Looks like paomo.

657
00:28:18,070 --> 00:28:19,330
Will it hold the paper?

658
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,590
It's paste made from flour.

659
00:28:21,590 --> 00:28:23,000
We've always used it at home.

660
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:24,350
It's sticky and lasts a long time.

661
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:25,350
And when removed,

662
00:28:25,350 --> 00:28:27,480
it won't leave marks on the door or wall.

663
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:28,400
You can try it later.

664
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:29,130
Works great.

665
00:28:29,270 --> 00:28:30,800
You're really good at this.

666
00:28:30,880 --> 00:28:31,790
Impressive.

667
00:28:32,960 --> 00:28:34,000
Bottom line's yours.

668
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:34,790
Mine?

669
00:28:34,810 --> 00:28:37,000
Yes, help me think of one.
It's still blank.

670
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:37,590
Alright.

671
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:41,000
"One shovel divides
longitude and latitude."

672
00:28:44,430 --> 00:28:45,320
Let me see.

673
00:28:50,350 --> 00:28:50,920
Got it.

674
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:54,400
"Two young hearts connect as one."

675
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:55,310
The horizontal line is

676
00:28:55,310 --> 00:28:56,310
"Love on the job."

677
00:28:57,310 --> 00:28:57,970
How's that?

678
00:28:58,830 --> 00:28:59,590
You're so...

679
00:29:00,010 --> 00:29:01,810
Who's in love on the job with you?

680
00:29:01,830 --> 00:29:02,110
Wait.

681
00:29:02,110 --> 00:29:02,880
You even flipped your hair.

682
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:04,720
Can't you be serious for once?

683
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:05,720
Serious for what?

684
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:07,030
Serious for what, Ms. Luo?

685
00:29:07,030 --> 00:29:08,720
-You're really blending in around here.
-Stop it.

686
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:09,500
Listen...

687
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:13,510
Dad.

688
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:14,750
Mom.

689
00:29:17,590 --> 00:29:18,520
It's cold today.

690
00:29:18,650 --> 00:29:19,920
Let's skip washing the noodles.

691
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:20,960
-Just have it.
-Here, Fang.

692
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:21,350
Thanks, Auntie.

693
00:29:21,350 --> 00:29:23,350
Here you go. You like strong flavor.

694
00:29:23,500 --> 00:29:25,310
Extra spoonful for you.

695
00:29:25,350 --> 00:29:26,440
Dad still knows me best.

696
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:27,590
Of course.

697
00:29:27,590 --> 00:29:29,180
Uncle, Auntie, let's drink.

698
00:29:29,180 --> 00:29:29,510
Okay.

699
00:29:30,310 --> 00:29:31,170
Here, sweetie.

700
00:29:31,550 --> 00:29:33,160
Don't forget to drink the noodle soup.

701
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:35,070
It's good for digestion and the stomach.

702
00:29:35,070 --> 00:29:36,160
That's all pseudoscience.

703
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:37,330
Experts have already debunked it.

704
00:29:37,330 --> 00:29:40,170
It's old wisdom from our ancestors.

705
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:40,750
Luo,

706
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:42,250
give Qing

707
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:44,200
more cucumbers.

708
00:29:44,310 --> 00:29:46,000
Look at her hands. It's peeling.

709
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:46,400
Alright.

710
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,680
She must be lacking vitamins.

711
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:48,440
Alright. Here.

712
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:49,400
Sweetie, have more.

713
00:29:49,400 --> 00:29:50,590
Auntie, would you like some?

714
00:29:50,590 --> 00:29:52,240
Sure. I can handle two shots.

715
00:29:52,240 --> 00:29:52,480
Okay.

716
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:53,790
Mom, if that's true,

717
00:29:53,790 --> 00:29:54,550
with all my heart palpitations,

718
00:29:54,550 --> 00:29:56,680
shouldn't I have heart disease by now?

719
00:29:57,010 --> 00:29:58,520
You silly girl,

720
00:29:58,550 --> 00:30:00,030
why can't you stop

721
00:30:00,030 --> 00:30:01,240
talking nonsense?

722
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:01,880
Listen,

723
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:03,510
don't get mad at her.

724
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:04,570
It's the New Year.

725
00:30:05,510 --> 00:30:07,240
We haven't spent the last
two Spring Festivals together.

726
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:07,830
It's okay,

727
00:30:07,830 --> 00:30:09,880
It's been a while since Mom smacked me.

728
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:11,080
You're asking for it.

729
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:14,750
Your dad always plays
the good guy in front of you.

730
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:17,640
While I'm cooking and serving—

731
00:30:17,860 --> 00:30:19,400
guess who ends up the bad guy?

732
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:20,160
Sweetheart.

733
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:21,720
How can you say that?

734
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,480
Look, I've been eating this whole time.

735
00:30:23,480 --> 00:30:25,030
You're the real hero today.

736
00:30:25,750 --> 00:30:26,350
Is it good?

737
00:30:26,350 --> 00:30:26,750
Yea...

738
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:27,590
I haven't eaten yet.

739
00:30:27,590 --> 00:30:28,590
Fang, eat more.

740
00:30:28,590 --> 00:30:29,310
Come on, eat up.

741
00:30:29,310 --> 00:30:29,880
Okay.

742
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,510
How about we raise glasses?

743
00:30:31,590 --> 00:30:32,590
Okay. Come on, cheers!

744
00:30:32,590 --> 00:30:35,030
-Uncle and Auntie, welcome to Qinchuan.
-Cheers.

745
00:30:35,030 --> 00:30:35,720
Thank you.

746
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:36,030
Alright.

747
00:30:36,030 --> 00:30:38,310
Today we're having
noodles with soybean paste and wine.

748
00:30:38,310 --> 00:30:40,200
The more we eat, the better the year!

749
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,000
One more thing.

750
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:42,160
Let me say something.

751
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:43,360
Happy New Year, okay?

752
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:44,510
Okay, come on.

753
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:45,540
Wish you all...

754
00:30:45,550 --> 00:30:47,750
Happy New Year!

755
00:30:47,830 --> 00:30:48,300
Good.

756
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:51,110
Well,

757
00:30:51,830 --> 00:30:52,560
Captain Luo,

758
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:55,240
I'll head back after I finish eating.

759
00:30:56,100 --> 00:30:57,760
Why are you suddenly leaving?

760
00:30:58,480 --> 00:30:59,680
I miss my parents too.

761
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:01,350
Right.

762
00:31:01,640 --> 00:31:02,440
Let him go back.

763
00:31:02,440 --> 00:31:03,200
It's the New Year after all.

764
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:03,680
Right.

765
00:31:04,070 --> 00:31:04,470
Right.

766
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:15,400
Mr. Mu,

767
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:18,490
are you satisfied with this cover design?

768
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:19,650
It's quite good.

769
00:31:19,810 --> 00:31:20,940
Simple and elegant.

770
00:31:22,050 --> 00:31:22,160
[Appreciation of Black Pottery Figurines]

771
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:23,110
Should we invite

772
00:31:23,110 --> 00:31:25,110
a celebrity to endorse the preface?

773
00:31:25,310 --> 00:31:26,590
I heard the Qinchuan

774
00:31:26,590 --> 00:31:28,830
Antiques Association just
appointed a new president—

775
00:31:28,830 --> 00:31:31,240
Zhao Youlin from the Mingde Museum.

776
00:31:31,480 --> 00:31:32,740
How about I invite him?

777
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:33,480
Him?

778
00:31:34,030 --> 00:31:34,960
Better not.

779
00:31:35,550 --> 00:31:38,070
He can't even explain
what a black pottery figurine is.

780
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:39,800
What can we expect him to write?

781
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:41,550
It's better to rely on ourselves
than to ask others.

782
00:31:41,550 --> 00:31:42,950
I've already written it.

783
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:44,560
By the way,

784
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:45,680
what do you think

785
00:31:46,110 --> 00:31:47,270
about the first print run?

786
00:31:47,270 --> 00:31:48,200
100,000 copies.

787
00:31:50,550 --> 00:31:52,010
That's not a small number.

788
00:31:52,310 --> 00:31:54,750
It'll cost nearly two million
to self-publish.

789
00:31:54,750 --> 00:31:57,350
How can we measure
cultural value with money?

790
00:31:58,070 --> 00:31:59,920
Mr. Peng, just print as I said.

791
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:01,440
I want these

792
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:02,550
100,000 copies

793
00:32:02,550 --> 00:32:04,640
in every bookstore across Qinchuan.

794
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:06,960
You really have a heart of gold.

795
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:07,880
Mr. Mu,

796
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:10,590
with your passion for cultural relics,

797
00:32:10,590 --> 00:32:12,960
you're destined to lead

798
00:32:12,960 --> 00:32:14,890
the collecting world in Qinchuan.

799
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:16,310
I'm flattered.

800
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:19,510
This book only offers a general overview.

801
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:21,660
I'll still need your help

802
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:23,480
organizing the launch event.

803
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,590
Don't worry.

804
00:32:25,750 --> 00:32:28,110
I promise the book launch
will be a big deal.

805
00:32:28,110 --> 00:32:29,680
I can assure you,

806
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:30,720
I'll get some real

807
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,470
heavyweight guests to attend.

808
00:32:33,830 --> 00:32:34,400
However,

809
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:38,450
let's forget about those
pretentious people who feign knowledge.

810
00:32:38,750 --> 00:32:40,000
We're not on the same level, after all.

811
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:42,440
The people I find for you
will definitely be professionals.

812
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:44,070
Remember I told you
about my friend's cousin,

813
00:32:44,070 --> 00:32:45,600
the one who was involved in

814
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:48,550
bringing the black pottery figurines
back to China?

815
00:32:48,550 --> 00:32:49,750
How about I invite him?

816
00:32:49,750 --> 00:32:50,550
From the archaeological team?

817
00:32:50,550 --> 00:32:50,950
Right.

818
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:51,860
That works.

819
00:32:51,970 --> 00:32:53,970
It's a good chance to learn from him.

820
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:56,920
Shilin.

821
00:32:56,920 --> 00:32:57,510
Peng.

822
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:58,880
Long time no see.

823
00:32:58,880 --> 00:32:59,790
Long time no see.

824
00:32:59,790 --> 00:33:00,920
Please, have a seat.

825
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:04,110
I've been busy with
a lot of things at home lately.

826
00:33:04,110 --> 00:33:05,570
Sorry to keep you waiting.

827
00:33:05,790 --> 00:33:06,960
Don't mention it.

828
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:10,830
About that journal submission
you asked about last time—

829
00:33:10,830 --> 00:33:11,960
I've asked about it.

830
00:33:12,190 --> 00:33:12,850
No problem.

831
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:13,330
Easy.

832
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:15,010
Then I...

833
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:16,920
I must thank you properly.

834
00:33:17,750 --> 00:33:19,790
Now I need a favor from you too.

835
00:33:20,270 --> 00:33:21,600
Something a bit tricky.

836
00:33:22,270 --> 00:33:23,160
What's the matter?

837
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:25,290
Could you give a public lecture about

838
00:33:25,590 --> 00:33:28,590
the cultural background
of black pottery figurines?

839
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:31,960
I have a friend who's
organizing a public lecture.

840
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:32,470
Mr. Guo,

841
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:35,110
I've already promised this to him.

842
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:35,790
Don't let me

843
00:33:35,790 --> 00:33:37,250
make a fool of myself then.

844
00:33:38,270 --> 00:33:40,200
A public lecture on archaeology?

845
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:43,750
I fully

846
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:45,590
support that.

847
00:33:53,350 --> 00:33:54,410
How about this one?

848
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:55,110
And this one.

849
00:33:55,110 --> 00:33:56,480
Your kid's already in elementary school—

850
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:57,880
who's going to read this book?

851
00:33:57,880 --> 00:33:59,000
Parents these days pick books

852
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:01,750
that match their child's
cognitive development.

