00:34:01,750 --> 00:34:03,810
They call it "calcium for the brain."

854
00:34:04,110 --> 00:34:05,840
I still enjoy books like this,

855
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,030
and I don't seem to lack calcium.

856
00:34:07,030 --> 00:34:07,740
You don't lack calcium—

857
00:34:07,740 --> 00:34:09,000
you lack common sense.

858
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:12,620
You always get so anxious
when facing problems.

859
00:34:12,690 --> 00:34:13,760
I think you were mentally underdeveloped

860
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,070
when you were a child.

861
00:34:29,150 --> 00:34:31,659
[New Book "Appreciation of Black Pottery Figurines"
Now On Sale]

862
00:34:31,739 --> 00:34:33,920
[Mu Jianhui]

863
00:34:47,440 --> 00:34:48,500
Look at this crowd.

864
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:50,130
It's quite a scene here.

865
00:34:50,889 --> 00:34:52,600
See? I wasn't joking.

866
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:55,460
Peng Cheng,

867
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:57,980
who is this Mu Jianhui anyway?

868
00:34:58,230 --> 00:35:00,440
He's the folk scholar I told you about—

869
00:35:00,710 --> 00:35:02,280
specializes in Han figurines.

870
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:03,010
He organized this book signing event.

871
00:35:03,010 --> 00:35:05,480
[Mu Jianhui's New Book Signing Event]

872
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:07,760
I know all the scholars
in Han figurine studies.

873
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:09,090
Never heard of this guy.

874
00:35:10,070 --> 00:35:12,130
That's why I said he's a folk scholar.

875
00:35:12,670 --> 00:35:14,440
You're always stuck in your ivory tower.

876
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:16,350
How would you know about these matters?

877
00:35:16,350 --> 00:35:17,480
Didn't you ask me here

878
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:19,800
to help promote archaeology lectures?

879
00:35:34,510 --> 00:35:35,230
Let me tell you,

880
00:35:35,230 --> 00:35:37,110
we archaeologists don't
get involved in collecting.

881
00:35:37,110 --> 00:35:39,570
Getting mixed up
in these things is not good.

882
00:35:40,070 --> 00:35:40,840
Don't worry.

883
00:35:42,150 --> 00:35:42,800
All you need to do is

884
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:45,070
share some knowledge
about black pottery figurines.

885
00:35:45,070 --> 00:35:46,130
Just talk about it.

886
00:35:47,130 --> 00:35:48,860
Come on, would I ever set you up?

887
00:35:49,070 --> 00:35:49,630
Peng.

888
00:35:50,700 --> 00:35:51,590
Mr. Mu, nice to see you again.

889
00:35:51,590 --> 00:35:52,880
Nice to see you again, Mr. Mu.

890
00:35:52,880 --> 00:35:54,280
Let me introduce for you.

891
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:01,710
This is the one I told you about,

892
00:36:01,710 --> 00:36:05,630
our Qinchuan Han figurine expert,
Mr. Mu Jianhui.

893
00:36:05,710 --> 00:36:06,570
You flatter me.

894
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:09,150
I've heard so much about you, Mr. Guo.

895
00:36:09,630 --> 00:36:11,760
Today I finally have the chance
to learn from you.

896
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:13,360
I've just published a book

897
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:15,030
introducing black pottery figurines.

898
00:36:15,030 --> 00:36:16,690
Please give me your guidance.

899
00:36:18,030 --> 00:36:19,440
I think it's about time.

900
00:36:19,590 --> 00:36:21,230
Mr. Guo, let's head up to the stage.

901
00:36:21,230 --> 00:36:21,800
Let's go.

902
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:23,930
Go ahead, it's fine.

903
00:36:24,230 --> 00:36:25,190
You've got a wealth of knowledge—

904
00:36:25,190 --> 00:36:26,690
share some with the audience.

905
00:36:26,690 --> 00:36:27,220
Let's go.

906
00:36:32,070 --> 00:36:33,070
Hello, everyone.

907
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:34,590
Welcome to

908
00:36:34,590 --> 00:36:37,710
Mr. Mu Jianhui's new book signing event.

909
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:39,840
This book,
"Appreciation of Black Pottery Figurines,"

910
00:36:39,840 --> 00:36:42,920
is the result of six years
of dedicated research,

911
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:44,530
revised five times

912
00:36:44,710 --> 00:36:46,400
and written with great passion.

913
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:48,920
Today, we're also honored to have invited

914
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:52,630
Mr. Guo Shilin
from the Qinchuan Cultural Relics
Protection

915
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:53,880
and Archaeology Institute

916
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:55,150
to give us a talk about

917
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:56,710
the culture of black pottery figurines.

918
00:36:56,710 --> 00:36:57,480
How about that?

919
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:58,360
Good.

920
00:37:01,070 --> 00:37:01,920
Good.

921
00:37:02,670 --> 00:37:03,710
Hello, everyone.

922
00:37:04,110 --> 00:37:06,000
We're especially honored
today to have invited

923
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:08,150
such a heavyweight guest as Mr. Guo.

924
00:37:08,670 --> 00:37:10,870
So let me start by asking you a question.

925
00:37:11,550 --> 00:37:12,070
Mr. Guo,

926
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:15,820
when did you first
hear about black pottery figurines?

927
00:37:17,760 --> 00:37:18,620
A few years ago,

928
00:37:19,670 --> 00:37:21,480
at an overseas auction.

929
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:23,070
There were six
black pottery figurines at that time.

930
00:37:23,070 --> 00:37:24,930
Yeah, what a coincidence. Me too.

931
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:26,370
I still remember

932
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:28,240
the starting bid at that time was

933
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:29,800
$800 per piece.

934
00:37:30,550 --> 00:37:32,110
But due to some special reasons,

935
00:37:32,110 --> 00:37:33,640
the auction was called off.

936
00:37:34,230 --> 00:37:35,400
If it had continued,

937
00:37:35,960 --> 00:37:37,760
I believe the final price

938
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:40,070
would have been over $1,500.

939
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:41,940
In today's market,

940
00:37:41,940 --> 00:37:43,200
it would be priceless.

941
00:37:54,590 --> 00:37:55,250
Captain Qi.

942
00:37:57,150 --> 00:37:59,920
What's going on with Mr. Guo Shilin?

943
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:02,420
Why is he supporting a Relics Dealer?

944
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:03,230
What?

945
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:07,200
How did he get
mixed up with a Relics Dealer?

946
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:09,670
I saw him at the Han-Tang Cultural Space

947
00:38:11,070 --> 00:38:12,870
helping someone sell a new book.

948
00:38:13,480 --> 00:38:14,480
The book is about

949
00:38:15,070 --> 00:38:17,920
how to appraise black pottery figurines.

950
00:38:18,150 --> 00:38:18,630
What?

951
00:38:19,630 --> 00:38:22,070
Why are national treasures
called national treasures?

952
00:38:22,070 --> 00:38:24,800
They must have outstanding cultural value.

953
00:38:25,230 --> 00:38:26,670
Take black pottery figurines for example.

954
00:38:26,670 --> 00:38:28,000
Why are they so valuable?

955
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:29,330
Because they're black.

956
00:38:29,510 --> 00:38:30,880
And why are they black?

957
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:33,030
Because they were burned in a fire

958
00:38:33,030 --> 00:38:34,800
during the Western Jin Dynasty.

959
00:38:34,800 --> 00:38:36,230
Mr. Guo, am I right?

960
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:40,480
Yes, they were burned indeed.

961
00:38:41,630 --> 00:38:44,630
That's a trace of history

962
00:38:44,630 --> 00:38:46,190
left on the artifact.

963
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:49,510
To establish yourself
in the collection market,

964
00:38:49,510 --> 00:38:50,970
you must understand this.

965
00:38:51,230 --> 00:38:53,090
If you don't, you'll get scammed.

966
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:55,630
That's also why I wrote this book.

967
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:57,800
To decode the value of artifacts

968
00:38:58,070 --> 00:39:00,840
from a historical
and cultural perspective.

969
00:39:01,630 --> 00:39:02,670
Back to the point—

970
00:39:03,320 --> 00:39:06,280
why do black pottery figurines
have collectible value?

971
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:08,360
First, their unique black color.

972
00:39:09,230 --> 00:39:11,320
Second, their origin.

973
00:39:11,960 --> 00:39:12,760
And for that,

974
00:39:12,980 --> 00:39:15,020
we must consult Mr. Guo.

975
00:39:15,630 --> 00:39:16,230
Why?

976
00:39:16,840 --> 00:39:19,590
Because his current
excavation site is precisely where

977
00:39:19,590 --> 00:39:22,650
black pottery figurines
were unearthed—Yin Village.

978
00:39:22,710 --> 00:39:24,310
This Mu guy is quite cunning.

979
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:26,560
He's setting Guo up.

980
00:39:26,590 --> 00:39:27,840
What burial level or rank

981
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:29,370
these figurines belong to?

982
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:32,400
Whether he answers or not,

983
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:35,400
he's become a supporter of
his black pottery figurine collection.

984
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:36,320
Mr. Guo didn't answer.

985
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:37,840
It seems he thinks my question

986
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:39,070
is too elementary

987
00:39:39,550 --> 00:39:41,840
to be worth answering.

988
00:39:42,510 --> 00:39:45,190
So, let me answer for him.

989
00:39:46,230 --> 00:39:47,630
Black pottery figurines are actually

990
00:39:47,630 --> 00:39:49,360
clothed pottery figurines.

991
00:39:49,710 --> 00:39:51,510
Mr. Guo Shilin

992
00:39:51,880 --> 00:39:52,920
coming here

993
00:39:53,270 --> 00:39:55,200
has actually added to his prestige

994
00:39:56,960 --> 00:39:58,360
and increased his value.

995
00:39:58,480 --> 00:39:59,440
Think about it.

996
00:39:59,840 --> 00:40:02,170
Can burial objects from an emperor's tomb

997
00:40:02,190 --> 00:40:04,960
be compared with those
from a commoner's tomb?

998
00:40:05,670 --> 00:40:07,000
From an emperor's tomb?

999
00:40:09,480 --> 00:40:10,000
Mr. Mu,

1000
00:40:10,510 --> 00:40:12,310
I disagree with your statement.

1001
00:40:12,470 --> 00:40:13,070
Is that so?

1002
00:40:13,550 --> 00:40:15,750
Which part of what I said was incorrect?

1003
00:40:16,150 --> 00:40:16,710
Aren't

1004
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:19,810
the black pottery figurines
from an emperor's tomb?

1005
00:40:20,230 --> 00:40:21,440
I've also heard that

1006
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:25,760
a large tomb was discovered where the
black pottery figurines were unearthed.

1007
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:27,550
It's even in the shape
of the character "亚".

1008
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:30,110
If not an emperor's tomb,
what else could it be?

1009
00:40:30,110 --> 00:40:31,150
The tomb's in the shape
of the character "亚".

1010
00:40:31,150 --> 00:40:32,000
In the shape of the character "亚"?

1011
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:33,330
That's quite a big deal.

1012
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:35,130
That must be an emperor's tomb.

1013
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:38,000
Regardless of where
the black pottery figurines came from,

1014
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,060
we archaeologists

1015
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:42,320
only care about their
historical and cultural value.

1016
00:40:42,320 --> 00:40:43,920
As for collecting and money—

1017
00:40:44,110 --> 00:40:44,630
sorry,

1018
00:40:44,880 --> 00:40:45,740
not my concern.

1019
00:40:46,030 --> 00:40:48,800
I'm Fang Kun, a colleague of Mr. Guo.

1020
00:40:50,230 --> 00:40:50,880
Mr. Fang,

1021
00:40:50,900 --> 00:40:51,880
hello.

1022
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:53,080
You're right.

1023
00:40:53,590 --> 00:40:55,760
If we only measure collections by money,

1024
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:57,550
that would be too narrow-minded.

1025
00:40:57,550 --> 00:40:59,710
In fact, many of us who collect artifacts

1026
00:40:59,710 --> 00:41:02,360
do it to preserve human civilization,

1027
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:04,730
to bring ancient Chinese culture

1028
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:06,000
to the world.

1029
00:41:06,110 --> 00:41:08,150
Don't try to change the subject here.

1030
00:41:08,150 --> 00:41:08,710
I didn't come here today

1031
00:41:08,710 --> 00:41:11,240
to debate
the meaning of collecting with you.

1032
00:41:11,880 --> 00:41:13,760
I just want to ask you one question.

1033
00:41:13,760 --> 00:41:15,760
How did our black pottery figurines

1034
00:41:15,760 --> 00:41:17,290
end up at a foreign auction?

1035
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:26,150
If you can't answer, I will.

1036
00:41:27,670 --> 00:41:29,000
Through tomb robbing.

1037
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:30,970
Through smuggling.

1038
00:41:31,440 --> 00:41:33,440
Through shameless cultural theft.

1039
00:41:34,670 --> 00:41:36,760
Anyone who promotes
black pottery figurine collecting today

1040
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:38,510
is supporting tomb raiders,

1041
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:40,530
whitewashing relics dealers,

1042
00:41:40,800 --> 00:41:43,480
and fueling this dirty trade chain.

1043
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:46,030
I'm not against collecting,

1044
00:41:46,710 --> 00:41:48,230
but I firmly oppose

1045
00:41:48,230 --> 00:41:50,560
equating artifacts with monetary value.

1046
00:41:52,160 --> 00:41:54,090
I've skimmed through your book.

1047
00:41:54,510 --> 00:41:55,670
It clearly encourages

1048
00:41:55,670 --> 00:41:57,130
profit-driven behavior.

1049
00:41:57,400 --> 00:41:58,280
It will only

1050
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:01,000
stimulate tomb robbing and smuggling.

1051
00:42:01,480 --> 00:42:03,840
Do tomb raiders only steal an artifact?

1052
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:05,030
No.

1053
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:08,520
What they steal is a witness to history,

1054
00:42:08,840 --> 00:42:10,240
the key to civilization.

1055
00:42:10,950 --> 00:42:11,400
Good!

1056
00:42:11,760 --> 00:42:12,030
Good!

1057
00:42:12,030 --> 00:42:12,630
Well said!

1058
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:13,230
Good!

1059
00:42:13,510 --> 00:42:13,960
Good!

1060
00:42:14,110 --> 00:42:14,510
Good!

1061
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:19,460
Guo Shilin!

1062
00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:23,820
You really screwed me over this time.

1063
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:28,260
Alright, let's give a round of applause
to send off Mr. Guo.

1064
00:42:31,100 --> 00:42:32,150
That went okay today.

1065
00:42:32,150 --> 00:42:32,850
Yeah.

1066
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:33,480
Mr. Mu.

1067
00:42:34,320 --> 00:42:34,980
Captain Qi,

1068
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:36,710
You head back first.

1069
00:42:36,710 --> 00:42:37,670
-Okay.
-I'll go say hello.

1070
00:42:37,670 --> 00:42:38,280
Alright, I'm leaving.

1071
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:38,710
Okay.

1072
00:42:40,630 --> 00:42:41,290
Captain Qi,

1073
00:42:41,710 --> 00:42:43,440
so you attended my lecture too?

1074
00:42:44,230 --> 00:42:46,190
I should call you Expert Mu now.

1075
00:42:46,500 --> 00:42:47,530
Don't tease me.

1076
00:42:49,710 --> 00:42:53,110
Confucius only
passed on knowledge and never created—

1077
00:42:53,700 --> 00:42:56,220
and here you're
writing books at your age.

1078
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:58,320
I have to learn from you.

1079
00:42:58,360 --> 00:42:59,400
I'm so flattered.

1080
00:42:59,710 --> 00:43:01,670
Is there anything
you don't want me to hear?

